OL,4,CColonial Pipeline boss confirms $4.4m
OL,5,Cransom payment
OL,6, Colonial Pipeline has confirmed it paid
OL,7, a $4.4m (#3.1m) ransom to the
OL,8, cyber-criminal gang responsible for
OL,9, taking the US fuel pipeline offline.
OL,11,FIts boss told the Wall Street Journal
OL,12,Fhe authorised the payment on 7 May
OL,13,Fbecause of uncertainty over how long
OL,14,Fthe shutdown would continue.
OL,16,F"I know that's a highly controversial
OL,17,Fdecision," Joseph Blount said in his
OL,18,Ffirst interview since the hack.
OL,20,FThe 5,500-mile (8,900-km) pipeline
OL,21,Fcarries 2.5 million barrels a day.
